theorem Topology.interior_union_open_right_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A U : Set X} (hU : IsOpen U) :
    interior (A ∪ U) = interior A ∪ U := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (A ∪ U) ⊆ interior A ∪ U`
    intro x hx
    by_cases hxU : x ∈ U
    · -- If `x ∈ U`, we are done.
      exact Or.inr hxU
    · -- Otherwise `x ∉ U`; we show `x ∈ interior A`.
      -- Choose an open neighbourhood `V` of `x` contained in `A ∪ U`.
      rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hx with ⟨V, hVopen, hxV, hVsub⟩
      -- Consider the open set `W = V \ U`.
      have hWopen : IsOpen (V \ U) := hVopen.diff hU
      have hxW    : x ∈ V \ U      := ⟨hxV, hxU⟩
      -- Show that `W ⊆ A`.
      have hWsub  : (V \ U) ⊆ A := by
        intro y hy
        have hyV : y ∈ V := hy.1
        have hyAU : (y : X) ∈ A ∪ U := hVsub hyV
        cases hyAU with
        | inl hA  => exact hA
        | inr hU' => exact (hy.2 hU').elim
      -- Hence every point of `W` lies in `interior A`.
      have hWint : (V \ U) ⊆ interior A :=
        interior_maximal hWsub hWopen
      -- In particular, `x ∈ interior A`.
      have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := hWint hxW
      exact Or.inl hxIntA
  · -- `interior A ∪ U ⊆ interior (A ∪ U)`
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxIntA =>
        -- `interior A` is contained in `interior (A ∪ U)` by monotonicity.
        exact
          (interior_mono (Set.subset_union_left : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ U)) hxIntA
    | inr hxU =>
        -- The open set `U` is contained in `interior (A ∪ U)`.
        have hSub : (U : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ U) :=
          interior_maximal
            (by
              intro y hy
              exact Or.inr hy)
            hU
        exact hSub hxU

theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_iterate_five_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  simpa [Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior]

theorem Topology.P3_union_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (interior A ∪ interior B) := by
  -- Both `interior A` and `interior B` are open,
  -- hence their union is open as well.
  have h_open : IsOpen (interior A ∪ interior B) :=
    (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A)).union isOpen_interior
  -- Open sets satisfy `P3`.
  exact
    Topology.isOpen_implies_P3
      (X := X)
      (A := interior A ∪ interior B)
      h_open
